cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper proposes a novel CNN-based framework for skull stripping in infant MR images. This involves image segmentation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed framework also introduces a new loss function and data augmentation technique, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.MM.
